19/05/2004
THESSALONIKI, Greece -- Albanian Ambassador Bashkim Zeneli met on Tuesday (18 May) with the Director General of the Thessaloniki Police, General Nikiforos Tzatzakis. They discussed the case of three Albanian emigrants who were killed by a Greek citizen. Police recently detained Yannis Baltas on charges of murder and abduction; he later confessed to killing the three Albanians in 1995 and 1996. (ATA - 18/05/04)
